\title{FOSBAAS: Functions and Data for Sports Business Analytics}
\description{
The FOSBAAS package is the companion to the book \emph{Fundamentals of Sports
Business Analytics and Strategy}. It provides the example data sets used in
the book along with the simulation and helper functions that created them.
}
\details{
The functions favour clarity over robustness: they have minimal error
checking and are meant to illustrate a single idea from the book rather than
to be used in production.
}
\section{Data sets}{

The package ships pre-built data describing a fictional sports franchise,
including \link{customer_data}, \link{demographic_data}, \link{season_data},
\link{manifest_data}, \link{secondary_data}, \link{customer_renewals}, \link{aggregated_crm_data},
\link{fa_survey_data}, \link{perceptual_data}, \link{scan_data}, \link{wait_times_data},
\link{wait_times_distribution_data}, \link{freq_table_data} and \link{freq_table_data_bin}.
Because \code{LazyData} is enabled, each is available by name once the package is
attached.
}

\section{Simulation helpers}{

Functions are grouped into families that mirror the book's chapters:
\itemize{
\item Season simulation -- \code{\link[=f_build_season]{f_build_season()}} and its helpers.
\item Customer & demographic simulation -- \code{\link[=f_build_demographic_data]{f_build_demographic_data()}} and helpers.
\item Lead scoring -- \code{\link[=f_create_lead_scoring_data]{f_create_lead_scoring_data()}} and helpers.
\item Operations & queueing -- \code{\link[=f_get_MMKN]{f_get_MMKN()}}, \code{\link[=f_get_wait_times]{f_get_wait_times()}}, \code{\link[=f_get_scan_data]{f_get_scan_data()}}.
\item Small utilities -- \code{\link[=f_add_zero]{f_add_zero()}}, \code{\link[=f_define_line]{f_define_line()}}, \code{\link[=f_build_freq_table]{f_build_freq_table()}}.
}
